article.description: — Heru Bligen's 17 points helped Fairleigh Dickinson defeat LIU 82-75 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Bligen puts up 17, Fairleigh Dickinson knocks off LIU 82-75
article.linkText: Bligen puts up 17, Fairleigh Dickinson knocks off LIU 82-75
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- — Heru Bligen's 17 points helped Fairleigh Dickinson defeat LIU 82-75 on Thursday night. Bligen had four steals for the Knights (11-12, 5-3 Northeast Conference). Ansley Almonor scored 16 points while shooting 5 for 13, including 4 for 7 from beyond the arc. Sean Moore had 15 points and shot 5 for 13 (3 for 9 from 3-point range) and 2 of 4 from the free throw line. Tai Strickland led the way for the Sharks (4-16, 3-5) with 21 points and seven rebounds. Nikola Djapa added 19 points, nine rebounds and two steals for LIU. In addition, Tana Kopa had 18 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
